WEBVTT

1
00:00:08.008 --> 00:00:11.554
[indistinct voices speaking]

2
00:00:11.637 --> 00:00:13.639
[woman speaking over P.A.]

3
00:00:18.811 --> 00:00:20.813
- [indistinct chatter]
- [TV playing]

4
00:00:25.192 --> 00:00:27.194
[exhales]

5
00:00:31.073 --> 00:00:32.742
[sighs]

6
00:00:35.995 --> 00:00:37.997
[sighs heavily]

7
00:00:45.045 --> 00:00:47.089
Can I sit down?

8
00:00:47.173 --> 00:00:49.175
Hi. Frank.

9
00:00:50.384 --> 00:00:52.386
Hey. you.

10
00:00:55.222 --> 00:00:57.224
[groans softly]

11
00:01:01.187 --> 00:01:03.189
I'm okay.

12
00:01:05.232 --> 00:01:07.359
You feel safe here. right?

13
00:01:08.944 --> 00:01:11.322
Yeah. me. too.

14
00:01:11.405 --> 00:01:13.491
Felt the same way.

15
00:01:14.575 --> 00:01:17.369
You don't have to stay here.

16
00:01:19.789 --> 00:01:22.500
I couldn't see a way out.

17
00:01:22.625 --> 00:01:24.376
[laughs]

18
00:01:24.460 --> 00:01:26.587
Join the club.
I couldn't. either.

19
00:01:26.670 --> 00:01:29.006
[laughs]

20
00:01:29.089 --> 00:01:32.343
You just want
to run and get out.

21
00:01:32.426 --> 00:01:35.262
But there's nowhere to go.

22
00:01:41.936 --> 00:01:44.939
You were right
about Uncle George.

23
00:01:47.441 --> 00:01:49.693
I didn't want to be.

24
00:02:04.834 --> 00:02:06.126
[exhales]

25
00:02:06.210 --> 00:02:08.212
I love you.

26
00:02:10.381 --> 00:02:12.591
Okay.

27
00:02:15.302 --> 00:02:18.055
[indistinct P.A. announcement]

28
00:02:18.138 --> 00:02:20.140
♪ ♪

29
00:02:28.315 --> 00:02:29.900
[siren wails in distance]

30
00:02:29.984 --> 00:02:32.736
- [indistinct chatter]
- [footsteps approaching]

31
00:02:46.333 --> 00:02:48.878
You got to be shitting me.

32
00:02:54.925 --> 00:02:57.428
That's a whole other story.
So how is she?

33
00:03:00.514 --> 00:03:02.516
She's fine.

34
00:03:03.559 --> 00:03:05.936
She's gonna be fine.

35
00:03:06.020 --> 00:03:09.231
[Billy] Well. George got her
to agree to a 5150.

36
00:03:09.315 --> 00:03:11.609
They've got her for 72 hours.

37
00:03:12.693 --> 00:03:15.404
What a major
fucking prick he is.

38
00:03:15.487 --> 00:03:18.157
Your brother tried to kill me.

39
00:03:20.993 --> 00:03:22.995
Were you surprised?

40
00:03:23.078 --> 00:03:25.706
- No.
- I'm not the least bit fucking surprised.

41
00:03:25.789 --> 00:03:27.875
Well. I-I just don't
understand it.

42
00:03:27.958 --> 00:03:29.251
I mean. why would he do that?

43
00:03:29.335 --> 00:03:31.170
He's got Kate and he's winning.

44
00:03:32.421 --> 00:03:35.215
Winning isn't enough for George.

45
00:03:35.299 --> 00:03:38.218
Will you testify?

46
00:03:41.722 --> 00:03:43.724
♪ ♪

47
00:03:45.017 --> 00:03:47.019
[entry bells jingle]

48
00:03:55.527 --> 00:03:56.862
What do you say. Lisa?

49
00:03:56.946 --> 00:03:58.572
Hey. Billy.

50
00:03:58.656 --> 00:04:00.616
You all right?

51
00:04:00.699 --> 00:04:02.826
Same old. same old.

52
00:04:02.910 --> 00:04:05.704
Clean hand today.
thank goodness.

53
00:04:05.788 --> 00:04:08.290
So just a little shot
of mother's milk will do me.

54
00:04:08.374 --> 00:04:10.626
Sure you didn't rub
that off yourself?

55
00:04:10.709 --> 00:04:13.128
[chuckles] Nope.

56
00:04:13.212 --> 00:04:16.006
He went easy on me.

57
00:04:18.717 --> 00:04:21.053
Lady's buying.

58
00:04:30.104 --> 00:04:31.730
Spring roll?

59
00:04:31.814 --> 00:04:33.565
They're actually quite good.

60
00:04:33.649 --> 00:04:35.484
No. thanks.

61
00:04:35.567 --> 00:04:38.320
You sure you want
to be seen with me?

62
00:04:38.404 --> 00:04:41.156
We can keep our distance.
so to speak.

63
00:04:41.240 --> 00:04:43.200
Please.

64
00:04:51.208 --> 00:04:53.419
How can I help you?

65
00:04:53.502 --> 00:04:55.355
Oh. I think you've done quite
a bit already. haven't you?

66
00:04:55.379 --> 00:04:57.548
Been a busy little bee.
gumming up the works.

67
00:05:00.300 --> 00:05:03.053
The judge voided
our Zax Pharma settlement.

68
00:05:03.137 --> 00:05:04.722
Really. what happened?

69
00:05:04.805 --> 00:05:07.182
[laughs] Please.
like you don't know.

70
00:05:07.266 --> 00:05:09.852
Well. you fired me.
I'm off the case.

71
00:05:09.935 --> 00:05:12.688
I'm enjoying my unemployment
and doing a little sightseeing

72
00:05:12.771 --> 00:05:14.898
- in the meantime.
- Lovely.

73
00:05:14.982 --> 00:05:17.484
- Shame I can't read your travelogue.
- Mm.

74
00:05:17.568 --> 00:05:19.028
Not until after the trial.

75
00:05:19.111 --> 00:05:20.320
Of course.

76
00:05:21.655 --> 00:05:24.450
Well. McBride.
you continue to enjoy yourself.

77
00:05:24.533 --> 00:05:27.161
And I will continue
to pay your rent

78
00:05:27.244 --> 00:05:29.413
just as long you need to...

79
00:05:29.496 --> 00:05:31.081
sightsee.

80
00:05:31.165 --> 00:05:32.833
Well. that's
awfully kind of you.

81
00:05:32.916 --> 00:05:34.918
[chuckles] Kindness has
nothing to do with it.

82
00:05:35.002 --> 00:05:37.296
I don't like you.

83
00:05:38.338 --> 00:05:40.716
You like me a little bit.

84
00:05:44.094 --> 00:05:46.346
This case has developed a stink.

85
00:05:46.430 --> 00:05:48.223
and you sniffed it out
long before I did.

86
00:05:48.307 --> 00:05:50.309
so I have no choice.

87
00:05:50.392 --> 00:05:52.561
I have to trust
and your instincts.

88
00:05:52.644 --> 00:05:54.063
Okay.

89
00:05:54.146 --> 00:05:55.939
And quite frankly...

90
00:05:56.023 --> 00:05:57.775
I'm afraid.

91
00:05:57.858 --> 00:05:59.526
Afraid of what?

92
00:05:59.610 --> 00:06:01.111
Sam.

93
00:06:02.362 --> 00:06:04.948
Her reaction
to Tom's death was...

94
00:06:05.032 --> 00:06:07.534
odd. cold.

95
00:06:08.911 --> 00:06:11.455
And I had a dream
that night that she...

96
00:06:11.538 --> 00:06:13.332
slit my throat

97
00:06:13.415 --> 00:06:15.250
with a pearl-handled
letter opener.

98
00:06:15.334 --> 00:06:17.336
Which I'm sure
she's wanted to do

99
00:06:17.419 --> 00:06:18.962
ever since I married her father.

100
00:06:19.046 --> 00:06:20.881
But...

101
00:06:20.964 --> 00:06:23.092
she's never quite disturbed

102
00:06:23.175 --> 00:06:24.885
my sleep like that before.

103
00:06:26.345 --> 00:06:29.389
Yeah. I've been having
a few dark dreams myself.

104
00:06:29.473 --> 00:06:31.225
Do you survive them?

105
00:06:32.810 --> 00:06:34.019
I don't know yet.

106
00:06:34.103 --> 00:06:36.188
I'm still waiting to see.

107
00:06:42.361 --> 00:06:44.905
Is Sam compromised?

108
00:06:46.365 --> 00:06:48.617
Unfortunately. yeah.

109
00:06:56.208 --> 00:06:57.918
Fuck.

110
00:07:01.630 --> 00:07:03.423
What do I do?

111
00:07:03.507 --> 00:07:05.717
The only person
that can save Sam

112
00:07:05.801 --> 00:07:07.803
from this is Sam.

113
00:07:11.223 --> 00:07:13.725
[footsteps approaching]

114
00:07:13.809 --> 00:07:17.229
- [knocking]
- Hey. you.

115
00:07:17.312 --> 00:07:20.190
Benefits from Tom True's
life insurance policy.

116
00:07:20.274 --> 00:07:21.900
They need your signature
for the release.

117
00:07:21.984 --> 00:07:23.152
No. they don't.

118
00:07:23.235 --> 00:07:25.529
Then consider it a formality.

119
00:07:25.612 --> 00:07:27.298
I don't want to be
the lone signatory on this.

120
00:07:27.322 --> 00:07:28.615
It's too damn awful.

121
00:07:30.117 --> 00:07:31.618
Come in.

122
00:07:39.126 --> 00:07:41.128
[sighs]

123
00:07:42.462 --> 00:07:45.549
I can still hear
Tom whistling in the hallway.

124
00:07:45.632 --> 00:07:47.801
the way he did... his tuneless.

125
00:07:47.885 --> 00:07:49.761
phantom whistling.

126
00:07:49.845 --> 00:07:52.681
I'll never understand
why he decided to go like this.

127
00:07:54.975 --> 00:07:57.269
Christ. what was he thinking?

128
00:07:57.352 --> 00:07:59.062
Well. that's the thing
about suicide.

129
00:07:59.146 --> 00:08:01.899
You just never know.

130
00:08:03.567 --> 00:08:06.111
There is another matter
to discuss.

131
00:08:06.195 --> 00:08:08.197
Oh. yeah?

132
00:08:10.657 --> 00:08:12.993
Your life insurance policy.

133
00:08:13.076 --> 00:08:14.536
What about it?

134
00:08:14.620 --> 00:08:16.997
Well. with Tom gone.
it would be financially prudent

135
00:08:17.080 --> 00:08:18.665
to increase your premiums.

136
00:08:18.749 --> 00:08:20.292
However. your...

137
00:08:20.375 --> 00:08:22.920
multiple sclerosis is
a complication.

138
00:08:23.003 --> 00:08:25.672
Ava. you do what you need to do.

139
00:08:27.966 --> 00:08:30.219
You'll probably be the last
Margolis standing anyway.

140
00:08:30.302 --> 00:08:31.929
Yes.

141
00:08:32.012 --> 00:08:34.097
And who's to say
I wouldn't shutter the firm

142
00:08:34.181 --> 00:08:37.017
before the ink is dried
on your own benefits check.

143
00:08:38.518 --> 00:08:40.103
Because you wouldn't do that.

144
00:08:40.187 --> 00:08:41.980
- Wouldn't I?
- No.

145
00:08:42.064 --> 00:08:43.315
It's my father's firm.

146
00:08:43.398 --> 00:08:45.275
My husband's firm.

147
00:08:46.818 --> 00:08:48.362
And I will continue
to honor his legacy

148
00:08:48.445 --> 00:08:50.197
even if you don't.

149
00:08:54.326 --> 00:08:57.329
Get the fuck out
of my office now.

150
00:08:58.789 --> 00:09:00.791
- Thank you for this.
- Oh. you're welcome.

151
00:09:07.714 --> 00:09:10.217
[exhales]

152
00:09:12.970 --> 00:09:14.721
Oh. thank God. Peter.

153
00:09:14.805 --> 00:09:16.515
- Give it to me.
- Hey. Patty.

154
00:09:19.643 --> 00:09:21.812
You want some gum?

155
00:09:21.895 --> 00:09:23.939
- What?
- Some gum?

156
00:09:24.022 --> 00:09:25.691
No. I'm set. thank you.

157
00:09:25.774 --> 00:09:28.819
Yeah. I tried the patches.
but they make me feel weird.

158
00:09:28.902 --> 00:09:30.904
Cool.

159
00:09:34.825 --> 00:09:36.827
[clears his throat]

160
00:09:39.997 --> 00:09:42.249
You lost your witness.

161
00:09:42.332 --> 00:09:44.209
Excuse me?

162
00:09:44.293 --> 00:09:46.962
Kate Zax. she's out.

163
00:09:47.045 --> 00:09:49.214
I'm sorry. who the fuck are you?

164
00:09:49.298 --> 00:09:51.341
- I'm the messenger.
- What?

165
00:09:51.425 --> 00:09:53.802
Her uncle had her locked up.
5150 psychiatric hold.

166
00:09:53.885 --> 00:09:55.762
Jesus Christ.
when did that happen?

167
00:09:55.846 --> 00:09:57.514
Don't know. Didn't ask.

168
00:09:57.597 --> 00:09:59.158
You got a meeting set up
for you tonight.

169
00:09:59.182 --> 00:10:01.476
You got all the details there.

170
00:10:02.686 --> 00:10:04.956
- Who am I meeting?
- I don't know. I'm just the messenger.

171
00:10:04.980 --> 00:10:07.149
Make sure you're not followed.
Last call.

172
00:10:07.232 --> 00:10:08.817
I don't want your gum. man!

173
00:10:08.900 --> 00:10:10.986
- Sure? All right. okey-doke.
- Yes! Shit!

174
00:10:14.698 --> 00:10:17.534
Peter?

175
00:10:17.617 --> 00:10:19.619
Thank you.

176
00:10:19.703 --> 00:10:22.414
♪ ♪

177
00:10:25.417 --> 00:10:27.419
Fuck.

178
00:10:29.838 --> 00:10:31.798
Hey. listen. I got
something wrong with the key.

179
00:10:31.882 --> 00:10:34.134
- I can't get in.
- Well. it's all clear down here.

180
00:10:34.217 --> 00:10:37.262
I mean. you still have some time
to figure it out.

181
00:10:38.347 --> 00:10:39.681
Just try the neighbors. then.

182
00:10:39.765 --> 00:10:41.141
- All right.
- [knocking]

183
00:10:42.851 --> 00:10:44.144
[chuckles]

184
00:10:44.227 --> 00:10:45.562
Can I help you?

185
00:10:45.645 --> 00:10:47.189
Uh. Margaret. right?

186
00:10:47.272 --> 00:10:49.524
- Carol.
- Carol. right. right.

187
00:10:49.608 --> 00:10:51.336
Carol. I think I saw you in
the hallway with Tom one day.

188
00:10:51.360 --> 00:10:53.236
- Oh. maybe. yeah.
- So anyway...

189
00:10:53.320 --> 00:10:55.822
uh. I'm supposed to get some
stuff out of Tom's apartment

190
00:10:55.906 --> 00:10:57.574
for him. but I can't
get him on the phone.

191
00:10:57.657 --> 00:10:59.010
And he gave me
the wrong stupid key.

192
00:10:59.034 --> 00:11:00.577
- so I was just gonna see...
- Oh!

193
00:11:00.660 --> 00:11:02.079
is there any way I can...?

194
00:11:02.162 --> 00:11:03.914
You want to use my fire escape?

195
00:11:03.997 --> 00:11:06.249
- That'd be great.
- Okay. well. come on in.

196
00:11:06.333 --> 00:11:08.377
- Thank you. thank you very much.
- Okay.

197
00:11:08.460 --> 00:11:10.170
Sure.

198
00:11:10.253 --> 00:11:12.255
[♪ The Seven Ups:
"Bello at Night"]

199
00:11:30.440 --> 00:11:32.567
[Brittany] No way!
Kenny?

200
00:11:32.651 --> 00:11:34.027
Oh. my God!

201
00:11:34.111 --> 00:11:35.862
I knew it was you!
I saw you from. like.

202
00:11:35.946 --> 00:11:37.989
a mile away. I swear
I have. like. eagle eyes.

203
00:11:38.073 --> 00:11:39.366
What the hell are you doing

204
00:11:39.449 --> 00:11:41.284
- in San Francisco. dude?
- I'm sorry...

205
00:11:41.368 --> 00:11:42.970
Don't tell me that you don't
remember me. because if you

206
00:11:42.994 --> 00:11:44.472
don't remember. then what
does that say about me?

207
00:11:44.496 --> 00:11:45.747
- Right?
- Do I know you?

208
00:11:45.831 --> 00:11:48.125
You don't remember me
from the wedding?

209
00:11:48.208 --> 00:11:49.936
I'm not insulted. but I'm. like.
lowkey mad just a little bit.

210
00:11:49.960 --> 00:11:51.878
You look very handsome.
by the way. Really?

211
00:11:51.962 --> 00:11:53.147
- I'm sorry. I...
- Oh. my hair was different.

212
00:11:53.171 --> 00:11:54.482
I mean. I don't know
if you. like.

213
00:11:54.506 --> 00:11:55.983
still have that "girlfriend"
or whatever. but...

214
00:11:56.007 --> 00:11:57.926
- [Ken] I have work to do.
- No. it's fine.

215
00:11:58.009 --> 00:12:00.029
It's fine. I know we're busy.
We're all busy. right?

216
00:12:00.053 --> 00:12:01.555
So what... Oh. whoops.

217
00:12:01.638 --> 00:12:02.848
Did I drop my
earring in here?

218
00:12:02.931 --> 00:12:04.558
Hey. Billy.

219
00:12:04.641 --> 00:12:06.143
Work out okay?

220
00:12:06.226 --> 00:12:07.686
Oh. yes. thank you
very. very much.

221
00:12:07.769 --> 00:12:08.979
I got what I came for.

222
00:12:09.062 --> 00:12:10.564
Could I get you a drink?

223
00:12:10.647 --> 00:12:13.442
If I had time.
I really would. Carol.

224
00:12:13.525 --> 00:12:15.360
- But I. I'm. uh. kind of...
- Aw.

225
00:12:15.444 --> 00:12:16.862
I got to.
I got to get this to Tom.

226
00:12:16.945 --> 00:12:18.196
- Okay.
- Um. so... Okay.

227
00:12:18.280 --> 00:12:19.865
Next time. see you
in the hallway. huh?

228
00:12:19.948 --> 00:12:21.592
- Next time. yes.
- Good to see you. Billy.

229
00:12:21.616 --> 00:12:23.994
You. too. Carol.

230
00:12:32.961 --> 00:12:35.046
- Hey. Patty.
- What are you doing here?

231
00:12:35.130 --> 00:12:37.340
Well. I'm kind of stranded.

232
00:12:37.424 --> 00:12:39.468
Can I stay
at your place tonight?

233
00:12:39.551 --> 00:12:41.386
No!

234
00:12:41.470 --> 00:12:43.388
Oh.

235
00:12:43.472 --> 00:12:45.682
[♪ Skinshape: "After Midnight"]

236
00:12:45.765 --> 00:12:47.893
Cool.

237
00:12:47.976 --> 00:12:51.104
I'm busy as fuck
and I'm late for a thing.

238
00:12:51.188 --> 00:12:53.523
So can we talk in the car?

239
00:12:53.607 --> 00:12:56.109
So I can stay?

240
00:12:56.193 --> 00:12:58.111
Ooh. man.

241
00:12:58.195 --> 00:13:00.405
Does your mother know
you're in San Francisco?

242
00:13:00.489 --> 00:13:02.032
What does it matter?

243
00:13:02.115 --> 00:13:04.075
- Okay.
- [elevator bell dings]

244
00:13:04.159 --> 00:13:06.161
[Patty] All right.
what happened?

245
00:13:06.244 --> 00:13:08.139
- [Casey] Well. my dad said I could stay at his place.
- Uh-huh.

246
00:13:08.163 --> 00:13:10.415
But he wasn't home.

247
00:13:10.499 --> 00:13:12.876
He is in Cabo with Rhonda.

248
00:13:12.959 --> 00:13:15.253
Oh. fuck Rhonda. So he didn't
know you were coming?

249
00:13:15.337 --> 00:13:18.006
Well. I didn't want to give him
the opportunity to say no.

250
00:13:18.089 --> 00:13:20.008
That's smart.

251
00:13:20.091 --> 00:13:21.927
So here's the deal.

252
00:13:22.010 --> 00:13:23.595
You can stay with me tonight

253
00:13:23.678 --> 00:13:25.263
on one condition.

254
00:13:25.347 --> 00:13:27.547
You have to text your mother
and tell her where you are.

255
00:13:27.599 --> 00:13:29.184
Oh. come on!

256
00:13:29.267 --> 00:13:31.478
She doesn't give
a shit about me.

257
00:13:31.561 --> 00:13:34.064
I don't give a shit about your
feelings. Text your mother.

258
00:13:34.147 --> 00:13:35.291
Patty. I'm so tired
of her telling me

259
00:13:35.315 --> 00:13:36.775
that I'm wasting my life

260
00:13:36.858 --> 00:13:38.860
waiting tables.
not going to college.

261
00:13:38.944 --> 00:13:41.488
- I can't take it anymore.
- Look. I get it.

262
00:13:41.571 --> 00:13:43.508
I get it. Things are rough
with Christina right now.

